<P>It is probable he had an enthu&s;ia&s;tic turn. He took part with the puritans, who early beg<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n to give di&s;turbance to the church of <HI>England.</HI> Their &s;pirits were &s;o greatly e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">tered by the un|favorable conclu&s;ion of the mock conference between their <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">i+ni&s;ter<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> and the royal paedagogue, in 1603 <NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot"><HI>Rapin,</HI> ii 162.</NOTE>, that they gave <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ent
